00:26:36,870 --> 00:26:38,750
Jung Kyung.

261
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:42,020
What don't you like?

262
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:52,940
You guys should just decide the tempo and everything else. I'll just match whatever you decide.

263
00:26:55,370 --> 00:26:57,820
Of course...

264
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:02,090
Because you never have an opinion.

265
00:27:05,710 --> 00:27:10,300
Have you ever done anything the way you wanted?

266
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:15,480
Even once?

267
00:27:32,330 --> 00:27:34,530
Where are you going?

268
00:27:34,530 --> 00:27:36,340
Aren't you going to practice?

269
00:27:43,650 --> 00:27:44,510
Joon Young.

270
00:27:44,510 --> 00:27:47,610
Park Joon Young! Let's talk.

271
00:27:50,540 --> 00:27:52,560
About what?

272
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:01,280
Give me my birthday present.

273
00:28:02,510 --> 00:28:04,110
What?

274
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,200
My birthday present.

275
00:28:07,940 --> 00:28:09,940
It hasn't arrived.

276
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:17,100
Because I didn't send it.

277
00:28:18,610 --> 00:28:20,100
Why not?

278
00:28:22,410 --> 00:28:24,810
Why didn't you send it?

279
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,060
I told you already.

280
00:28:29,060 --> 00:28:31,920
I'll never play Traumerei again...

281
00:28:35,100 --> 00:28:36,870
Joon Young--

282
00:28:49,310 --> 00:28:50,970
Excuse me...

283
00:28:53,580 --> 00:28:55,290
Song Ah.

284
00:28:55,290 --> 00:28:56,900
Yes?

285
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:59,100
Let's have our meeting now.

286
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,250
Our meeting? Right now?

287
00:29:02,250 --> 00:29:05,510
Yes, to finish up what we started talking about.

288
00:29:09,250 --> 00:29:10,790
Sure.

289
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:14,980
Then... please come to our office for a moment.

290
00:29:51,020 --> 00:29:54,250
Are you all done practicing?

291
00:29:54,780 --> 00:29:56,350
Yes...

292
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:01,020
Song Ah, you can go now.

293
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:04,420
Excuse me?

294
00:30:04,420 --> 00:30:09,980
I... didn't really want to talk about work. I just

295
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:13,710
wanted to get out of that situation, so I grabbed you.

296
00:30:15,330 --> 00:30:18,180
I'll leave after staying here for a moment.

297
00:30:18,180 --> 00:30:20,510
In case I run into her as I'm going out.

298
00:30:24,870 --> 00:30:27,130
Thanks for your help.

299
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:31,260
It's nothing.

300
00:30:31,940 --> 00:30:34,360
I did the same thing before.

301
00:30:36,110 --> 00:30:38,160
Oh, that's right.

302
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:41,050
I guess we're the same now.

303
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:55,260
Bye.

304
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:08,030
♫  If I can't adjust to this,  ♫

305
00:31:08,030 --> 00:31:10,850
♫  how can I  ♫

306
00:31:10,850 --> 00:31:16,950
♫  come to forget you?  ♫

307
00:31:16,950 --> 00:31:21,090
   

308
00:31:21,090 --> 00:31:25,200
 This... has been very helpful. Thank you. 

309
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:27,640
♫   Come back to me a bit less late.   ♫

310
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:29,880
 I'll give it to you. 

311
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,300
 Keep it. 

312
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:36,130
♫   Even these tears that are falling  ♫

313
00:31:36,130 --> 00:31:39,920
♫   will become   ♫

314
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:46,710
♫   part of my last farewell to you, be well.    ♫

315
00:31:46,710 --> 00:31:52,220
♫   Only one, just one thing I hope you won't forget  ♫

316
00:31:52,220 --> 00:31:57,030
Song Ah!

317
00:31:57,030 --> 00:31:57,920
Hey.

318
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,910
- Are you clocking out? 
 - Yeah.

319
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:06,420
- Um...I have somewhere I need to be right now. 
 - Oh...

320
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:08,630
Go ahead.

321
00:32:08,630 --> 00:32:11,610
♫   These tears that have gotten cold   ♫

322
00:32:11,610 --> 00:32:16,570
- Hey, Song Ah! Are you okay? 
 - Huh?

323
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:18,690
♫  Come back to me   ♫

324
00:32:18,690 --> 00:32:21,210
The instrument I fixed... is it okay?

325
00:32:21,210 --> 00:32:22,680
♫  a bit less late  ♫

326
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:26,690
♫   Even these tears that are falling  ♫

327
00:32:26,690 --> 00:32:31,300
Yeah, it's fine.

328
00:32:31,300 --> 00:32:39,750
♫   part of my last farewell to you, be well.    ♫

329
00:32:50,100 --> 00:32:52,490
What are you doing?

330
00:32:52,490 --> 00:32:54,470
You're finally home?

331
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:08,680
You've had too much to drink.

332
00:33:09,490 --> 00:33:11,610
Spend the night.

333
00:33:29,210 --> 00:33:31,190
You...

334
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:35,950
What's going on between you and Jung Kyung?

335
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:41,500
What are you two doing together?

336
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:52,700
I'm sorry... again.

337
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:57,860
How long are you in Korea?

338
00:33:59,990 --> 00:34:01,990
Well...

339
00:34:01,990 --> 00:34:04,150
Until next summer?

340
00:34:06,220 --> 00:34:09,880
Why? Are you tired of me? Want me to leave?

341
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,920
Go.

342
00:34:21,650 --> 00:34:23,620
Please leave.

343
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,020
I said spend the night.

344
00:34:31,020 --> 00:34:33,030
I said forget it!

345
00:34:36,170 --> 00:34:38,380
Hey.

346
00:35:05,630 --> 00:35:07,020
What are you doing?

347
00:35:07,020 --> 00:35:11,660
Well, they say it's not good for you to keep the fan fixed while sleeping.

348
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:19,610
I set up the timer for you, so sleep well. I'm leaving.

349
00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:37,540
The wind stings my eyes...

350
00:35:43,430 --> 00:35:45,210
 Go. 

351
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:49,910
 Please leave. 

352
00:35:54,990 --> 00:35:58,060
 Song Ah, have you ever been to Korea Fine Arts Middle School? 

353
00:35:58,060 --> 00:36:01,450
No, I just graduated out of a normal middle school.

354
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:02,900
What about you?

355
00:36:02,900 --> 00:36:07,060
A few times long ago. For parent-teacher conferences.

356
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:14,630
 Joon Young went to school alone in Seoul, so whenever he got his report cards, I'd nag him about it a lot. 

357
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:20,620
Anyway, later on, if you have any questions, even if I'm not there, you can... huh?

358
00:36:20,620 --> 00:36:22,960
It's Joon Young's mother.

359
00:36:42,550 --> 00:36:47,230
   

360
00:36:47,230 --> 00:36:49,130
 Hello. 

361
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:51,990
 Hello. 

362
00:36:54,680 --> 00:36:57,530
I am Joo Sang Woo from Kyunghoo Card Company.

363
00:36:57,530 --> 00:37:00,980
- Yes, nice to meet you. I am Chae Song Ah. 
 - Ah!

364
00:37:02,230 --> 00:37:04,740
Y-you're the person I talked with over the phone!

365
00:37:04,740 --> 00:37:06,020
Yes, how do you do?

366
00:37:06,020 --> 00:37:07,760
Yes, how do you do?

367
00:37:09,770 --> 00:37:12,890
- Could I also get a business card...? 
 - Ah.

368
00:37:12,890 --> 00:37:14,720
I'm...

369
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:17,480
Ms. Song Ah is an intern.

370
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:20,210
Intern?

371
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:26,220
So you were an intern...

372
00:37:28,870 --> 00:37:34,750
When our Section Chief Park Seong Jae was in GyeongKukHwa University, I heard he was your superior.

373
00:37:34,750 --> 00:37:36,890
Oh, Y-yes yes. He was so much higher than me.

374
00:37:36,890 --> 00:37:42,700
When Section Chief Park first came to our foundation, he was just... like you.

375
00:37:42,700 --> 00:37:45,800
It reminds me of those days.

376
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:48,430
What do you mean that he was like me?

377
00:37:48,430 --> 00:37:52,000
When they're deputies like you, they're so cute, aren't they?

378
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:55,510
Of course, they worked hard. Without question.

379
00:37:55,510 --> 00:37:57,430
Yes...

380
00:37:58,660 --> 00:38:02,990
As for me, I, unfortunately, have external meetings I have to attend, so I must take my leave first.

381
00:38:02,990 --> 00:38:05,400
Any details you need to iron out concerning the event, you can direct here

382
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:07,860
to Ms. Chae Song Ah.

383
00:38:07,860 --> 00:38:09,830
Oh, yes. I understand.

384
00:38:11,030 --> 00:38:14,930
   

385
00:38:26,700 --> 00:38:29,130
Joon Young!

386
00:38:29,130 --> 00:38:31,110
You're here?

387
00:38:35,690 --> 00:38:38,790
You said Father had changed these days.

388
00:38:45,990 --> 00:38:48,380
I'm sorry.

389
00:38:48,380 --> 00:38:50,960
When do you need it by?

390
00:39:08,220 --> 00:39:11,620
This is where the students practice their music.

391
00:39:11,620 --> 00:39:13,070
Oh yes.

392
00:39:13,070 --> 00:39:17,190
- So you must have cleared away the piano here, right? 
 - Ah...

393
00:39:17,190 --> 00:39:19,340
It's not that we put it away, we never had one.

394
00:39:19,340 --> 00:39:22,740
The new piano comes in next month.

395
00:39:23,580 --> 00:39:24,960
Ah yes.

396
00:39:25,970 --> 00:39:28,380
- Just a moment. 
 - Ah yes.

397
00:39:28,380 --> 00:39:30,380
Yes, teacher?

398
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:35,620
Ah, miss... intern?

399
00:39:35,620 --> 00:39:37,630
Intern person?

400
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:40,600
- Excuse me? 
 - Oh it's just...

401
00:39:41,650 --> 00:39:44,530
When you called me.

402
00:39:44,530 --> 00:39:47,340
That is... I picked up the phone,

403
00:39:47,340 --> 00:39:50,270
you just randomly said "I'm sorry!" 
 (T/N he drops formal speech)

404
00:39:50,270 --> 00:39:52,970
So I was surprised.

405
00:39:52,970 --> 00:39:55,150
I mean, who could this be...

406
00:39:55,150 --> 00:39:58,120
that they would call me to say "I'm sorry"?

407
00:39:58,120 --> 00:40:00,420
That's what I thought.

408
00:40:01,230 --> 00:40:08,980
I'm just saying... the foundation would've struggled to stay afloat if it weren't for Kyunghoo Card's funds.

409
00:40:08,980 --> 00:40:12,430
So that must be why she was sorry.

410
00:40:17,510 --> 00:40:19,730
Mr. Park Joon Young!

411
00:40:23,070 --> 00:40:27,020
How... I was told you had other business to take care of today...

412
00:40:27,020 --> 00:40:30,110
This event by itself is insufficient, isn't it?

413
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:35,030
If you need to get your money's worth, tell that to me.

414
00:40:35,030 --> 00:40:36,550
I'll do whatever you ask.

415
00:40:36,550 --> 00:40:41,300
However... is that under the condition...

416
00:40:41,300 --> 00:40:45,030
that you speak so flippantly to an employee of the foundation?

417
00:40:53,790 --> 00:40:56,080
It was so nice to see you again, Joon Young.

418
00:40:56,080 --> 00:41:02,140
Right, Hyeon Ho visited some time ago. I heard that Jung Kyung finished her studies as well and was back?

419
00:41:02,140 --> 00:41:04,790
All three of you should visit together next time.

420
00:41:04,790 --> 00:41:06,410
Yes.

421
00:41:17,130 --> 00:41:21,170
That person... from the card company from earlier...

422
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:26,490
He was flaunting the money that the company was giving the foundation, right?

423
00:41:26,490 --> 00:41:28,780
That is why I lost my temper.

424
00:41:28,780 --> 00:41:31,440
"Is money everything?" I thought.

425
00:41:32,500 --> 00:41:38,540
But...I don't think I'm qualified to criticize others.

426
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:41,750
I'm just the same.

427
00:41:43,050 --> 00:41:45,780
Just because I make some money.

428
00:41:50,420 --> 00:41:55,340
I got it. Can you ask Joon Young if that's alright with him?

429
00:41:55,340 --> 00:41:58,340
He won't say no, but...

430
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:03,110
I'm in a meeting, so I'll call you again later.

431
00:42:03,110 --> 00:42:05,000
Yes.

432
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:09,380
Who was it? Joon Young?

433
00:42:10,520 --> 00:42:14,900
What is it? Did his father cause trouble again?

434
00:42:17,530 --> 00:42:20,230
Is he in Europe right now?

435
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:21,760
   

436
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:27,060
Joon Young is back in Korea.

437
00:42:54,620 --> 00:42:57,010
Why aren't you wearing the ring?

438
00:42:58,060 --> 00:43:03,650
Hyeon Ho seemed concerned about it.

439
00:43:05,460 --> 00:43:08,480
Aren't you the one who is concerned?

440
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:19,560
These days... you're a bit much.

441
00:43:21,020 --> 00:43:21,820
Huh?

442
00:43:21,820 --> 00:43:24,540
Not "a bit much", I actually don't like you.

443
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:32,370
Park Joon Young!

444
00:43:39,480 --> 00:43:41,810
Hurry up and get married.

445
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:49,100
I wanted to see you to say this.

446
00:43:51,830 --> 00:43:54,160
Are you really serious?

447
00:43:57,510 --> 00:43:59,370
It's a request.

448
00:44:13,750 --> 00:44:16,140
I reported this to Team Leader.

449
00:44:16,140 --> 00:44:20,650
So she is currently finalizing the arrangements now.

450
00:44:26,050 --> 00:44:30,920
Ah... I'm sorry.

451
00:44:30,920 --> 00:44:33,730
Will you really be alright with performing?

452
00:44:33,730 --> 00:44:36,500
You're on your sabbatical year.

453
00:44:36,500 --> 00:44:38,550
It's alright.

454
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:44,020
Then treat me to a meal next time.

455
00:44:45,470 --> 00:44:47,960
Yes, I will.

456
00:44:56,390 --> 00:45:00,420
You know what you talked about earlier?

457
00:45:01,690 --> 00:45:07,720
How you don't like it when people flaunt about giving money or helping someone, to get credit for it.

458
00:45:07,720 --> 00:45:10,720
But I think...

459
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:14,900
Everyone has that kind of desire in some way if you're human.

460
00:45:17,330 --> 00:45:19,800
When we choose a gift,

461
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:24,340
we look forward to the other person liking what we picked.

462
00:45:25,890 --> 00:45:29,100
It's the same when we help someone.

463
00:45:29,100 --> 00:45:32,410
Even if we aren't actually expecting anything from it,

464
00:45:32,410 --> 00:45:35,960
we hope for it to also be worthwhile

465
00:45:35,960 --> 00:45:38,370
at the same time.

466
00:45:39,690 --> 00:45:42,600
But the Director...

467
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:47,050
When she gave me the scholarship, she wasn't expecting anything from me.

468
00:45:52,410 --> 00:45:56,400
I don't know if I'm in any place to say this,

469
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:59,000
but the Director

470
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:03,510
must have wanted you to live happily while playing the piano.

471
00:46:04,340 --> 00:46:07,370
She probably did it because she wanted to see that.

472
00:46:10,270 --> 00:46:12,340
Happiness...

473
00:46:20,890 --> 00:46:23,020
Song Ah.

474
00:46:23,020 --> 00:46:24,520
Yes?

475
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:27,200
Should we have that meal today?

476
00:46:53,820 --> 00:46:58,950
Come to think of it, we've met twice today.

477
00:46:59,980 --> 00:47:01,810
That's true.

478
00:47:05,050 --> 00:47:07,470
I went to the school earlier

479
00:47:07,470 --> 00:47:09,690
because I finished my business early

480
00:47:09,690 --> 00:47:12,570
and I knew you'd still be there,

481
00:47:12,570 --> 00:47:16,880
so I thought I should see the venue of the event as well.

482
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:19,590
But I suddenly realized something.

483
00:47:19,590 --> 00:47:22,370
"I should go see Song Ah."

484
00:47:22,370 --> 00:47:27,670
"If I see her, I'll feel better."

485
00:47:36,410 --> 00:47:41,730
So, are you feeling better now?

486
00:47:41,730 --> 00:47:43,360
Yes.

487
00:47:45,980 --> 00:47:48,050
So thanks to you, I realized it.

488
00:47:48,050 --> 00:47:50,690
I was wrong.

489
00:47:55,470 --> 00:47:59,140
The reason why I went to the school earlier today,

490
00:47:59,140 --> 00:48:04,350
was actually because I wanted to smile.

491
00:48:05,500 --> 00:48:09,490
Because when I'm with you, I have a good time and always smile.

492
00:48:13,550 --> 00:48:16,920
I guess I wanted to see you.

493
00:48:24,490 --> 00:48:28,210
♫  Oh   ♫

494
00:48:28,210 --> 00:48:31,430
♫  Oh  ♫

495
00:48:32,550 --> 00:48:37,450
♫  Think about you, your everything  ♫

496
00:48:38,430 --> 00:48:43,540
♫  I wanna stay, always by your side  ♫

497
00:48:44,570 --> 00:48:49,230
♫  Watching a transparent you,  ♫

498
00:48:49,230 --> 00:48:55,410
♫  my lips call for you again  ♫

499
00:48:55,410 --> 00:49:01,400
♫  I thought you'd know even if I tried to hide my feelings  ♫

500
00:49:01,400 --> 00:49:07,610
♫   I thought if you saw my eyes, you'd feel my gaze   ♫

501
00:49:07,610 --> 00:49:15,230
♫  Though I always linger a few paces behind you like a fool  ♫

502
00:49:17,710 --> 00:49:21,160
♫  I'll be on your side  ♫

503
00:49:23,730 --> 00:49:27,990
♫  The more I look at you  ♫

504
00:49:27,990 --> 00:49:31,260
♫  Ooh  ♫

505
00:49:31,260 --> 00:49:39,170
♫  Tell my honestly, if you feel the same way  ♫

506
00:49:41,790 --> 00:49:42,730
♫  Tomorrow  ♫

507
00:49:42,730 --> 00:49:46,490
Whenever you perform, the audience likes it, don't they?

508
00:49:46,490 --> 00:49:48,410
I'm envious.

509
00:49:48,410 --> 00:49:51,060
That's not true.

510
00:49:51,060 --> 00:49:56,400
There are days when I'm not in the best condition, or days when I strangely can't really focus.

511
00:49:56,400 --> 00:50:00,020
Or days when the piano from the venue isn't in a good state.

512
00:50:00,020 --> 00:50:03,360
But, "There is no bad piano in this world,"

513
00:50:03,360 --> 00:50:06,960
"only bad pianists."

514
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:09,800
There is such a saying.

515
00:50:09,800 --> 00:50:14,840
So this is something I should cope with.

516
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:19,500
No matter my mood, or what piano I'm given,

517
00:50:19,500 --> 00:50:24,390
I need to always do my utmost to give the best performance.

518
00:50:28,290 --> 00:50:33,340
So it's the fate of a pianist, I guess.

519
00:50:35,120 --> 00:50:39,270
Fate... Yes.

520
00:50:39,270 --> 00:50:43,600
In any case, there are various reason as to why one might ruin a performance,

521
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:46,250
but the audience or the critics

522
00:50:46,250 --> 00:50:49,780
have no reason to know the pianist's personal circumstances.

523
00:50:49,780 --> 00:50:55,220
