00:53:35,480 --> 00:53:38,580
You didn't need to buy all of this! Just having you here is enough.

554
00:53:38,580 --> 00:53:40,510
Professor, shall we take some photos?

555
00:53:40,510 --> 00:53:42,040
Oh, yes, yes! Let's do that!

556
00:53:42,040 --> 00:53:43,420
 Come over here! 

557
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:46,980
 Jung Kyung! What are you doing? Come over here! 

558
00:53:46,980 --> 00:53:48,540
Yes.

559
00:53:50,460 --> 00:53:53,170
You, move over a bit. Come here.

560
00:53:53,170 --> 00:53:54,450
Jung Kyung, come here.

561
00:53:54,450 --> 00:53:56,780
Let's take a picture now!

562
00:53:56,780 --> 00:54:02,590
For every piano competition you enter, it's said that you have to practice for several long and torturous months in advance.

563
00:54:02,590 --> 00:54:09,080
 I'm curious how you were able to ceaselessly string back-to-back competitions for the past 6 to 7 years. 

564
00:54:09,080 --> 00:54:12,510
 Were you simply built for competitions? 

565
00:54:12,510 --> 00:54:15,990
Built for it? Surely, not. Um...

566
00:54:18,040 --> 00:54:22,030
 Piano competitions... were something I really hated. 

567
00:54:23,410 --> 00:54:27,180
 First place? Of course it's nice. 

568
00:54:27,180 --> 00:54:30,270
 At first I was happy. I'd even get reward money. 

569
00:54:30,270 --> 00:54:34,930
 But... after winning a few more awards... 

570
00:54:34,930 --> 00:54:38,430
I had to keep participating...

571
00:54:38,430 --> 00:54:41,750
 and I had to keep winning. 

572
00:54:41,750 --> 00:54:47,730
After a while...I hated the competitions more than death itself.

573
00:54:50,860 --> 00:54:52,920
Did you write this down?

574
00:54:53,860 --> 00:54:56,300
 Don't write it down. 

