00:54:56,300 --> 00:54:59,030
How could I tell the kids that?

576
00:55:09,450 --> 00:55:11,370
 Tell me. 

577
00:55:12,730 --> 00:55:16,270
I'll listen to you. Your story.

578
00:55:16,270 --> 00:55:21,060
I think I learned a lot from the preparations for these piano competitions.

579
00:55:21,060 --> 00:55:25,460
To do music... is to find one's own answers

580
00:55:25,460 --> 00:55:29,660
from within the sheet music.

581
00:55:29,660 --> 00:55:32,470
After 7 years, you've concluded the Chopin Piano Competition as your last.

582
00:55:32,470 --> 00:55:36,040
And now you are a traveling pianist.

583
00:55:36,040 --> 00:55:39,230
What is the life of the musician like,

584
00:55:39,230 --> 00:55:42,480
performing a couple of times a week on stage at every corner of the globe?

585
00:55:42,480 --> 00:55:47,150
The classical musician...is always alone.

586
00:55:48,380 --> 00:55:54,050
Of course, now I'm greeted by the performance team whenever I get off the airport or train station...

587
00:55:54,050 --> 00:55:56,340
but it wasn't like this at the beginning.

588
00:55:56,340 --> 00:55:59,880
What happens if you're sick alone?

589
00:56:02,120 --> 00:56:06,790
Even if I'm sick...I can't be sick.

590
00:56:07,700 --> 00:56:13,210
I'm the only one who can fill my role, and it's a huge loss for my team.

591
00:56:13,210 --> 00:56:15,780
 So what can I do? 

592
00:56:15,780 --> 00:56:21,750
Digestive aids, sleeping aids, and for severe days, anxiety medicine.

593
00:56:21,750 --> 00:56:24,250
I survived through drugs.

594
00:56:27,570 --> 00:56:30,360
Sometimes I think this...

595
00:56:32,160 --> 00:56:35,650
What horrible deed must I have done in a previous life...

596
00:56:37,500 --> 00:56:39,930
to live like this?

597
00:56:45,550 --> 00:56:50,090
 Isn't it such a great blessing... to live as a musician? 

598
00:56:50,090 --> 00:56:52,200
That's what I think.

599
00:56:53,710 --> 00:56:58,110
 During tough times when you had to give up the piano... 

600
00:56:58,110 --> 00:57:01,280
 You were granted a scholarship through the Kyunghoo Cultural Foundation... 

601
00:57:01,280 --> 00:57:03,430
 thus allowing you to continue playing the piano. 

602
00:57:03,430 --> 00:57:06,130
 If you had not met the Kyunghoo Cultural Center... 

603
00:57:06,130 --> 00:57:08,870
What kind of life would you be living now?

604
00:57:08,870 --> 00:57:12,700
Uh...

605
00:57:12,700 --> 00:57:17,040
It's a little hard...to imagine.

606
00:57:17,040 --> 00:57:21,410
 I suppose I would be doing...something, right? 

607
00:57:21,410 --> 00:57:24,190
Although it wouldn't be the piano.

608
00:57:25,060 --> 00:57:31,000
 I think...I would be a little freer. 

